title: Be conservative on what you do, be liberal on what you accept from others
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

You should be as stable and robust as possible by being able to take whatever in and have the same output.

In software engineering, a piece of code should be able to accept any kind of crazy input but be sturdy enough to return a valid output.